description: Naja, The main character of the book named herself Naja which roughly translates to "snake". She is cold blooded, calculated and deadly much like her namesake. She is the number 3 assassin of the gangster zero. Later in the story she learns that an old friend of hers is locked inside a colombian prison, and unlike her usual indifferent self, she decides to rescue him, showing that she may have some compassion after all.
name: Naja

description:
This series was part of the X-MEN REGENESIS crossover and was continued from Uncanny X-Men Vol.1. After the events of Schism, Uncanny X-Men started over with a new #1. It lasted for only 20 issues after which it was revamped after the events of Avengers Vs. X-Men as All-New X-Men Volume 1. Although All-New X-Men existed, a new volume of Uncanny X-Men (Vol. 3) started in February 2013, accompanying the before-mentioned title.

Collected Editions

  • Uncanny X-Men by Kieron Gillen Vol 1 (#1-4)

  • Siege: Battleworld (#9-10)

Find out in the first chapter of this four-issue series.
